  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "4:1-5 Every attempt to revive true religion will stir up the opposition of Satan, and of those in whom he works. The adversaries were the Samaritans, who had been planted in the land of Israel, 2Ki 17. It was plain that they did not mean to unite in the worship of the Lord, according to his word. Let those who discourage a good work, and weaken them that are employed in it, see whose pattern they follow.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ye have nothing to do with us - Because the Samaritans had united idolatrous rites with the worship of Yahweh ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 17:29-41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". To have allowed them a share in restoring the temple would have been destructive of all purity of religion.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As king Cyrus ... commanded us - The exact words of the edict gave the right of building exclusively to those who should \"go up\" from Babylonia to Judaea Ezra 1:3. ",
